{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781966774615,"sessionID":"ses_11a818b5dffer2YDz4na8QwbBS","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"157695127","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/private/tmp/tokenwarden-bench/2026-06-20T06-38-17-288Z/dcp-docs-from-code-3/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md"},"output":"<path>/private/tmp/tokenwarden-bench/2026-06-20T06-38-17-288Z/dcp-docs-from-code-3/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Cache API\n2: \n3: ## createCache()\n4: \n5: Creates a new cache instance with an internal `Map` for storing key-value pairs.\n6: \n7: ```js\n8: import { createCache } from 'path/to/cache'\n9: \n10: const cache = createCache()\n11: // cache is now an object with get, set, delete, and clear methods\n12: ```\n13: \n14: ### Methods\n15: \n16: The `createCache()` function returns an object with the following methods:\n17: \n18: #### get(key)\n19: \n20: Retrieves a value from the cache by its key. Returns the cached value if found, otherwise `undefined`.\n21: \n22: ```js\n23: cache.get('my-key')\n24: ```\n25: \n26: #### set(key, value)\n27: \n28: Stores a value in the cache under the specified key. Returns the provided value.\n29: \n30: ```js\n31: cache.set('my-key', 'my-value')\n32: ```\n33: \n34: #### delete(key)\n35: \n36: Removes an entry from the cache by its key. Returns `true` if the key existed, `false` otherwise.\n37: \n38: ```js\n39: cache.delete('my-key')\n40: ```\n41: \n42: #### clear()\n43: \n44: Empties the entire cache, removing all key-value pairs.\n45: \n46: ```js\n47: cache.clear()\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ## Usage\n51: \n52: ```js\n53: import { createCache } from 'cache.mjs'\n54: \n55: const cache = createCache()\n56: \n57: cache.set('user:1', { id: 1, name: 'Alice' })\n58: const user = cache.get('user:1')\n59: cache.delete('user:1')\n60: cache.clear()\n61: ```\n\n(End of file - total 61 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Cache API\n\n## createCache()\n\nCreates a new cache instance with an internal `Map` for storing key-value pairs.\n\n```js\nimport { createCache } from 'path/to/cache'\n\nconst cache = createCache()\n// cache is now an object with get, set, delete, and clear methods\n```\n\n### Methods\n\nThe `createCache()` function returns an object with the following methods:\n\n#### get(key)\n\nRetrieves a value from the cache by its key. Returns the cached value if found, otherwise `undefined`.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/private/tmp/tokenwarden-bench/2026-06-20T06-38-17-288Z/dcp-docs-from-code-3/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md","text":"# Cache API\n\n## createCache()\n\nCreates a new cache instance with an internal `Map` for storing key-value pairs.\n\n```js\nimport { createCache } from 'path/to/cache'\n\nconst cache = createCache()\n// cache is now an object with get, set, delete, and clear methods\n```\n\n### Methods\n\nThe `createCache()` function returns an object with the following methods:\n\n#### get(key)\n\nRetrieves a value from the cache by its key. Returns the cached value if found, otherwise `undefined`.\n\n```js\ncache.get('my-key')\n```\n\n#### set(key, value)\n\nStores a value in the cache under the specified key. Returns the provided value.\n\n```js\ncache.set('my-key', 'my-value')\n```\n\n#### delete(key)\n\nRemoves an entry from the cache by its key. Returns `true` if the key existed, `false` otherwise.\n\n```js\ncache.delete('my-key')\n```\n\n#### clear()\n\nEmpties the entire cache, removing all key-value pairs.\n\n```js\ncache.clear()\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```js\nimport { createCache } from 'cache.mjs'\n\nconst cache = createCache()\n\ncache.set('user:1', { id: 1, name: 'Alice' })\nconst user = cache.get('user:1')\ncache.delete('user:1')\ncache.clear()\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":61,"totalLines":61,"truncated":false}},"title":"bench-artifacts/cache-api.md","time":{"start":1781966774587,"end":1781966774611}},"id":"prt_ee57f1bdf001m3tFy2y064vdxP","sessionID":"ses_11a818b5dffer2YDz4na8QwbBS","messageID":"msg_ee57f17fe001JSiA0bOKNO6vgw"}}
